-- Monetary policy has exhausted itself: Fed's Fisher
-- 
-- Wed Jul 13, 2011 2:04pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/13/us-usa-fed-fisher-policy-idUSTRE76C5FQ20110713

 

 DALLAS  (Reuters) - U.S. monetary policy has "exhausted itself" and the Federal Reserve can do no more to boost the economy, a top Fed official said on Wednesday. 

 "We can tinker at the margins," Dallas Federal Reserve Bank President Richard Fisher told the Rotary Club of Dallas, but it is up to Congress to get the economy growing faster by addressing the budget deficit and U.S. debt problems. (Reporting by  Ann Saphir ; Editing by  James Dalgleish )